Pre-heat your #oven{} to 220 degrees. Chop the @sweet potato{1%small} into wedges roughly the width and length of your index finger. Put them on a #baking tray{}, drizzle over a good splash of @oil{}, sprinkle over half the @mild paprika{1.5%tsp}, a pinch of @salt{} and a grind of @black pepper{}. Make sure everything is evenly coated and put in your oven to cook for ~{25%minutes}.

Roughly chop the @coriander{1/2} (stalks and leaves!) and juice and zest the @lime{1}. Roughly chop the @salted peanuts{25}. Put the @British pork mince{300%g} in a #bowl{} and add three-quarters of your coriander along with your lime zest, peanuts, the other half of your paprika, half the @soy sauce{1}, a pinch of salt and a good grind of black pepper.

Combine everything together with your hands and shape into a burgers (one each), about 2cm thick.

> Don't make them too thick, they will change shape as the proteins tighten up while they are being cooked.

Remove the tough rooty bit off the @baby gem lettuce{1} and cut into roughly 2cm slices. Peel and grate the @carrot{1}, then mix it with your lettuce. In a bowl, mix the @olive oil{} with a dash of lime juice (don't use it all! You still need a bit of juice later on), a pinch of salt and pepper and whisk together with a #fork{}. Put most of your lettuce and carrot into the bowl with your limey dressing (reserve a little to put on your burgers!). Toss the salad.

Put a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add a splash of oil. Add your burgers and cook for ~{5%minutes} on each side, before placing them on a baking tray. Put the burgers in your oven to carry on cooking for ~{5%minutes} while you make the sauce.

> Your burgers are cooked through when they are no longer pink in the middle.

== Satay Sauce ==

For your satay sauce, put the @peanut butter{1} in a bowl and add your remaining lime juice. Add a splash of @water{} to loosen everything, together with the rest of your @soy sauce{} and coriander and mix with a fork.

> Only add as much lime as you like to taste.

== Assembly ==

Turn your #grill{} to high and cut each @brioche bun{2} in half.

> If your oven and grill aren't separate, just move your sweet potato and burgers down a shelf so the top shelf is free for grilling!

Put your buns under the grill for ~{1-2%minutes} on each side to toast them.

> Keep an eye on them, you don't want them to burn!

When everything is ready, spread your satay sauce on the bottom half of your bun, pop your burger on top, add some lettuce and carrot and pop the bun top on. Serve with a side of sweet potato wedges and your limey salad! YUM!